						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1735 (1813 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>States that <hi rend="italic">Tōḷiktniyāṉ</hi> (the palanquin) which was the offering of Vijayaraṅga-Chokkanātha-nāyaka to god Raṅganātha, having become dilapidated was repaired by Mr. George Francis Trevers, the Collector. The weight of gold used is 39(3/4) <hi rend="italic">seers</hi> and that of Silver 70(1/2) <hi rend="italic">seers.</hi> The record is <hi rend="bold">dated Śaka 1735, Śrīmukha, Kārttikka śu. 11, Bhṛiguvāra. The details of date</hi> correspond to <hi rend="bold">1813, A.D., November 4, Thursday.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
